WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.000
Downloaded From AnimeArcadia.lk

00:11.021 --> 00:13.188
[tense, mysterious music playing]

00:14.521 --> 00:16.688
All demon hunters have to take an oath.

00:17.646 --> 00:20.855
I swear to protect
the world from monsters,

00:20.938 --> 00:24.813
no matter how big,
or gross, or scary they are.

00:25.855 --> 00:27.188
I swear to protect--

00:27.271 --> 00:28.355
Shh!

00:28.438 --> 00:30.605
I think there's a demon outside.

00:49.521 --> 00:50.355
[snarls]

00:50.438 --> 00:52.230
[shrieking]

00:53.438 --> 00:54.646
[snarls]

00:58.771 --> 01:01.271
Mary, did you like the movie?

01:01.355 --> 01:03.938
It was okay. Not enough shooting.

01:04.021 --> 01:07.021
I told you not to let her watch
any more of those shoot-'em-ups.

01:07.105 --> 01:10.896
I just can't help giving my only daughter
everything she desires.

01:17.105 --> 01:18.480
[ominous music playing]

01:27.146 --> 01:29.271
John, that man is staring at us.

01:29.355 --> 01:30.855
I know. Walk faster.

01:37.563 --> 01:39.313
[music intensifies]

01:44.063 --> 01:44.896
Mary!

01:45.480 --> 01:49.646
I swear to protect the world
from monsters.

01:51.980 --> 01:52.980
Mary!

01:55.188 --> 01:57.230
[demon snarling]

01:59.938 --> 02:01.605
[train horn blaring]

02:05.146 --> 02:06.438
[Mary's mother whimpers]

02:12.521 --> 02:16.480
[officer] "A giant monster
with a face that opens in three pieces."

02:16.563 --> 02:19.313
Ha. Sure, buddy.
I'll get the sketch artist right on it.

02:19.396 --> 02:21.063
[officers laughing]

02:21.146 --> 02:22.355
[officer] Oh, yeah.

02:22.938 --> 02:23.938
[sighs]

02:24.021 --> 02:26.021
[tense, plaintive music playing]

02:27.688 --> 02:29.355
[loud clattering]

02:29.438 --> 02:32.813
[Mary's mother] I spoke to the college.
You haven't been to work in weeks.

02:32.896 --> 02:36.021
[John] This is my work.

02:36.105 --> 02:38.980
Don't you understand
that what we saw means my research,

02:39.063 --> 02:41.271
my theories about the other realm,
were right?

02:41.355 --> 02:44.021
Your daughter never sees you anymore!
I never see you!

02:44.105 --> 02:46.230
It's you that I'm doing this for.

02:46.730 --> 02:48.771
There are monsters breaching our world,

02:48.855 --> 02:51.355
and the authorities
can be relied on for nothing.

02:51.855 --> 02:53.771
I need to find a way to give myself power.

02:53.855 --> 02:55.396
Real power.

02:55.480 --> 02:58.271
So that I can protect this family.

02:58.355 --> 03:00.688
Like you protected us in the subway?

03:02.230 --> 03:04.563
John? John, I didn't mean that.

03:04.646 --> 03:06.855
It doesn't matter what you think of me.

03:12.146 --> 03:16.063
All that matters is the strength
to defeat the darkness that threatens us.

03:17.105 --> 03:18.105
Without that,

03:19.230 --> 03:20.480
we have nothing.

03:20.563 --> 03:21.480
[music trails off]

03:28.355 --> 03:30.646
["Rollin' (Air Raid Vehicle)"
by Limp Bizkit playing]

03:30.730 --> 03:32.521
♪ Throw your hands up ♪

03:32.605 --> 03:35.063
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

03:35.146 --> 03:37.813
♪ Throw your hands up
Throw your hands up ♪

03:37.896 --> 03:40.563
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:40.646 --> 03:42.980
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:43.063 --> 03:45.688
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:45.771 --> 03:47.855
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:47.938 --> 03:50.646
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:50.730 --> 03:53.063
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:53.146 --> 03:55.480
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:55.563 --> 03:58.063
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:58.146 --> 04:00.271
♪ Hey, ladies, hey, fellas ♪

04:00.355 --> 04:03.146
♪ And the people that don't give a **** ♪

04:03.230 --> 04:05.313
♪ All the lovers, all the haters ♪

04:05.396 --> 04:08.146
♪ And all the people
That call themselves players ♪

04:08.230 --> 04:10.230
♪ Hot mommas, pimp daddies ♪

04:10.313 --> 04:12.813
♪ And the people rollin' up in Caddies ♪

04:12.896 --> 04:15.771
♪ Hey, rockers, hip-hoppers ♪

04:15.855 --> 04:17.980
♪ And everybody all around the world ♪

04:18.063 --> 04:20.730
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

04:20.813 --> 04:23.230
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

04:23.313 --> 04:25.438
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

04:25.521 --> 04:28.105
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

04:28.188 --> 04:30.313
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

04:30.396 --> 04:33.105
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

04:33.188 --> 04:35.813
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

04:35.896 --> 04:36.896
[song trails off]

05:01.980 --> 05:05.146
Yo, lady! Not to be a backseat driver,

05:05.230 --> 05:08.313
but I'm pretty sure this violates
the Geneva Convention or something.

05:08.396 --> 05:11.355
[Mary] The Geneva Convention
only applies to humans.

05:12.146 --> 05:13.313
I'm a human!

05:13.396 --> 05:16.105
In your case,
I think the UN will understand.

05:16.605 --> 05:19.563
This has got to be
the second-worst job you ever gave me.

05:19.646 --> 05:22.480
Oh, you mean after the Raccoon City job?

05:23.063 --> 05:24.396
-Third-worst.
-Hmm.

05:25.146 --> 05:26.771
[Patriot] Patriot for Arkham.

05:26.855 --> 05:28.896
How're you liking
those new toys, Lieutenant?

05:28.980 --> 05:29.813
[guns trill, hum]

05:30.813 --> 05:31.646
Useful.

05:31.730 --> 05:33.438
Although it would have been more useful

05:33.521 --> 05:35.980
if you gave me this shit
before the mission.

05:36.063 --> 05:38.980
They're just a prototype
Goldstein whipped up in the lab.

05:39.063 --> 05:41.230
Not approved for field use yet.

05:41.313 --> 05:46.105
Uh, I got her other prototype
ready for you to test sometime too.

05:46.188 --> 05:47.021
[Mary] Can't wait.

05:47.896 --> 05:50.271
Sentry, King, what's your status?

05:50.355 --> 05:51.396
[Sentry] All good here.

05:51.480 --> 05:54.188
-We're being the best decoys we can be.
-[King] Good here too.

05:54.271 --> 05:57.855
Although I'm worried the doc's head
might explode from excitement.

05:58.521 --> 06:02.355
The transmitter works
precisely as I theorized, of course.

06:02.438 --> 06:05.271
It emits one half of
a quantum interference pattern.

06:05.355 --> 06:07.646
The rest of the pattern
comes from the amulet's other piece.

06:07.730 --> 06:12.355
So, if that thing is needed to destroy
the wall between us and the Demon Realm,

06:12.438 --> 06:14.063
how about we smash it right now?

06:14.146 --> 06:15.063
No!

06:15.146 --> 06:17.313
Absolutely no smashing it!

06:17.396 --> 06:21.771
The amulet's signal is actively
maintaining the quantum wall.

06:21.855 --> 06:24.563
The natural state of the two realms
is to be joined.

06:24.646 --> 06:26.188
If we destroy the transmitter,

06:26.271 --> 06:29.771
we don't know what would happen
to the stability of either universe.

06:30.271 --> 06:34.563
Not to mention
what we stand to gain from studying it.

06:34.646 --> 06:37.813
The potential applications
in quantum computing alone…

06:37.896 --> 06:40.063
Okay, okay, just asking.

06:40.146 --> 06:43.146
Uh, guys, let's get back to base
in one piece

06:43.230 --> 06:46.271
before we talk about
possibly destabilizing any universes.

06:47.105 --> 06:48.105
[Dante straining]

06:53.438 --> 06:54.355
[buckle twinkling]

06:55.438 --> 06:57.355
I've been in tough spots like this before.

06:57.438 --> 07:00.271
The trick is not to buckle
under the pressure.

07:01.271 --> 07:04.396
Hmm? Just give it up, Dante.

07:04.480 --> 07:05.855
It's over!

07:07.438 --> 07:10.146
Sure, they have their boots on our necks,

07:10.230 --> 07:12.938
but we need to buckle down,
and think positive.

07:14.105 --> 07:15.105
Uh…

07:16.105 --> 07:17.188
Ow!

07:17.271 --> 07:18.105
What the…

07:19.230 --> 07:20.855
-[buckle twinkles]
-Oh.

07:21.646 --> 07:24.563
-[agent] How are the prisoners?
-A little too fucking comfortable.

07:24.646 --> 07:25.646
[machinery hums]

07:27.271 --> 07:28.271
[both yelp]

07:28.355 --> 07:29.521
[Anders yelping]

07:35.938 --> 07:37.105
[Dante yelping]

07:37.188 --> 07:38.396
What was that for?

07:38.480 --> 07:42.188
Whoa! You gotta give me a warning
before you set off a flamethrower.

07:44.855 --> 07:45.938
[Dante grunts]

07:46.021 --> 07:48.521
If you, uh, don't mind, Lieutenant.

07:49.605 --> 07:53.063
So, do the fire jets
come standard on this model or…

07:53.146 --> 07:55.855
I've been in the market
for a flamethrower myself.

07:55.938 --> 07:58.313
Custom anti-demon upgrade.

07:58.396 --> 08:00.688
If the Hellblood somehow gets past those,

08:00.771 --> 08:03.521
there's always the nano-explosive
I injected him with,

08:03.605 --> 08:06.730
that's programmed to activate
if he gets outside of a one-mile radius.

08:07.480 --> 08:09.146
Even that thing
should have trouble healing

08:09.230 --> 08:11.480
from a bomb going off in its fucking neck.

08:11.563 --> 08:15.230
Damn! Yo, I'd hate to see
what you did to a full demon.

08:15.313 --> 08:17.313
Not to question your methods. At all.

08:17.396 --> 08:19.896
Don't tell me you have
a weak stomach, Anders.

08:19.980 --> 08:22.396
I'd have thought
you'd be rock hard for revenge

08:22.480 --> 08:24.688
after what the White Rabbit
did to your team.

08:25.730 --> 08:29.521
I… I'm just trying to make it home.
You know?

08:32.771 --> 08:33.605
Hmm.

08:33.688 --> 08:36.480
That's… unexpected.

08:36.563 --> 08:37.938
Something wrong?

08:38.021 --> 08:43.396
Not necessarily. It appears the pattern
coming from the transmitter is changing.

08:43.480 --> 08:45.896
Modulating itself for some reason.

08:49.563 --> 08:51.896
-You sure they cleared you for action?
-[haltingly] Oh, yeah.

08:51.980 --> 08:54.605
I'm good, Lieutenant. Solid. A-1.

08:55.896 --> 08:59.438
Lieutenant Arkham, this is Baines.
Report in.

08:59.521 --> 09:02.646
We're rolling smoothly, sir.
Should be home in under an hour.

09:02.730 --> 09:05.980
Good. With the fate
of Heaven and Earth at stake,

09:06.063 --> 09:07.855
there's no one else I would count on.

09:08.355 --> 09:10.480
-Patch me through to the prisoner.
-Sir?

09:10.563 --> 09:13.521
I want to speak with him. He interests me.

09:14.896 --> 09:15.813
-Dante.
-[Dante yelps]

09:15.896 --> 09:18.813
This is Vice President William Baines.

09:19.521 --> 09:23.396
The Vice President?
You mean, like, from TV?

09:23.480 --> 09:26.146
Boy, am I starting to regret
voting for this guy.

09:26.230 --> 09:29.105
I saw the footage
from the raid on your apartment.

09:29.771 --> 09:32.563
Your abilities are truly
a remarkable gift.

09:33.563 --> 09:35.980
Lieutenant Arkham tells me
you're part demon.

09:36.063 --> 09:37.146
[Dante] She's wrong.

09:37.230 --> 09:38.730
Yeah, I've got abilities.

09:38.813 --> 09:41.230
Maybe not exactly human ones, but they're…

09:41.313 --> 09:45.521
I don't know,
some sort of superhero mutations.

09:45.605 --> 09:48.021
Look, there's no part of me that's demon.

09:48.105 --> 09:49.146
There can't be.

09:49.646 --> 09:51.813
[Baines] Your mother and your brother,

09:51.896 --> 09:54.896
they were both killed by demons,
is that right?

09:55.980 --> 09:57.063
Yes.

09:57.146 --> 10:01.521
Yeah, yeah, yeah. We all have
dead families and traumatic childhoods.

10:02.980 --> 10:05.730
What? You think I talked?

10:05.813 --> 10:08.105
[laughing]

10:08.188 --> 10:09.438
Okay, I talked,

10:09.521 --> 10:11.521
but you should have seen
what they did to me!

10:11.605 --> 10:13.646
[Baines] What about your father, Dante?

10:13.730 --> 10:15.480
Couldn't tell you. I never met him.

10:16.646 --> 10:17.813
I see.

10:17.896 --> 10:21.230
There is demon blood in you,
that much is certain.

10:21.313 --> 10:24.105
You were born with
a black stain on your soul.

10:25.105 --> 10:28.438
But none of us are beyond God's light.

10:29.188 --> 10:32.021
He may still see fit
to cleanse that stain,

10:32.105 --> 10:34.438
should you prove yourself worthy of it.

10:35.605 --> 10:39.230
Sir, with all due respect,
you're wasting your time.

10:39.313 --> 10:42.438
It doesn't matter how much
of the demon's blood is unholy.

10:42.521 --> 10:45.230
Any is enough to make it a demon.

10:45.313 --> 10:47.563
Your passion is your strength, Mary.

10:47.646 --> 10:49.855
But don't allow it to blind you.

10:49.938 --> 10:53.396
Winning this war will take more
than anything human can provide.

10:53.480 --> 10:56.105
You've seen Dante's raw power.

10:56.188 --> 11:01.271
Imagine what that type of asset could do,
if used correctly.

11:01.771 --> 11:04.855
You want to use this thing?
Has the president approved that?

11:04.938 --> 11:08.896
All the president cares about
is maintaining his image.

11:08.980 --> 11:10.313
I set the policies.

11:11.396 --> 11:14.771
I bring the donors.
He approves what I tell him to.

11:15.271 --> 11:20.105
The Lord would not have sent us such
a powerful instrument to enact his will,

11:20.188 --> 11:23.355
if he did not intend for us to use it.

11:24.313 --> 11:25.313
[officer blows whistle]

11:27.938 --> 11:28.855
Road's closed.

11:28.938 --> 11:30.980
Looks like we're taking a detour.

11:35.021 --> 11:35.938
[gasps]

11:36.021 --> 11:37.563
[blows whistle]

11:38.730 --> 11:39.813
I'll go check it out.

11:48.938 --> 11:52.146
That's it.
That's what's causing the modulation.

11:52.230 --> 11:54.063
The signal adjusts in response

11:54.146 --> 11:56.438
to the other transmitter's
geospatial location

11:56.521 --> 11:58.355
to keep the overall pattern in sync.

11:58.438 --> 12:00.146
So the other amulet piece must be…

12:00.813 --> 12:01.813
[computer beeping]

12:01.896 --> 12:03.063
…getting closer.

12:03.855 --> 12:04.980
We stopped!

12:05.813 --> 12:06.980
This is our shot!

12:07.646 --> 12:09.230
Hurry up with that thing!

12:09.313 --> 12:10.730
[Dante] It's almost…

12:10.813 --> 12:12.771
[Mary] I figured you out, Hellblood.

12:12.855 --> 12:16.396
Do you really think this whole
jabbering moron act was going to work?

12:16.980 --> 12:19.813
Uh, maybe. What act are you talking about?

12:19.896 --> 12:21.855
[Mary] The one where you
don't know you're a demon?

12:21.938 --> 12:23.438
You just happen to be walking around

12:23.521 --> 12:25.605
with half the key to fucking Hell
on your neck?

12:25.688 --> 12:28.188
The key to Hell?
[chuckles] Whoa, whoa, whoa.

12:28.271 --> 12:31.146
I think you've all got
the wrong necklace. Seriously.

12:31.230 --> 12:33.438
It's just some old family heirloom
my mom gave me.

12:33.521 --> 12:34.896
[beeping rapidly]

12:38.313 --> 12:39.688
[all grunting]

12:45.980 --> 12:46.938
What happened?

12:47.021 --> 12:49.438
-[car horns blaring]
-[passersby clamoring]

13:10.521 --> 13:13.980
Whoever is left, protect the amulet.
That's an order.

13:14.605 --> 13:16.313
Protect it with your lives.

13:19.396 --> 13:20.563
We've got nothing.

13:21.146 --> 13:22.730
Did anyone else make it?

13:25.855 --> 13:27.105
We're clear.

13:27.188 --> 13:28.855
But there's no way to get to you.

13:32.980 --> 13:34.146
[Mary coughing]

13:43.980 --> 13:45.188
Are you okay?

13:45.271 --> 13:46.271
[groans] I think…

13:46.896 --> 13:48.396
my leg's stuck.

13:52.938 --> 13:54.521
-Not anymore.
-Fuck!

14:00.271 --> 14:02.730
What is this? Are we getting rescued?

14:02.813 --> 14:06.021
Can you think of anyone
who'd want to rescue either one of us?

14:06.105 --> 14:07.896
We ain't getting rescued!

14:10.563 --> 14:11.813
[uneasy music playing]

14:14.480 --> 14:16.521
Give it to me, I can protect it.

14:18.396 --> 14:19.396
It's the Rabbit!

14:19.480 --> 14:21.355
Does anyone have eyes on it?

14:21.438 --> 14:23.021
I have this area secure.

14:23.105 --> 14:24.605
[menacing voice] Do you now?

14:29.771 --> 14:33.355
Somehow, I truly doubt that.

14:34.105 --> 14:36.105
[forceful, dramatic rock music playing]

14:51.230 --> 14:54.063
Hey, demons! Big mistake!

14:54.146 --> 14:57.813
My boy Dante here
is going to whoop all your asses!

14:57.896 --> 14:59.688
What are you doing? [sputtering]

14:59.771 --> 15:01.438
Just one second!

15:01.521 --> 15:04.938
So, you want to surrender individually,

15:05.021 --> 15:06.188
or all at once?

15:06.688 --> 15:08.605
End her.

15:15.230 --> 15:17.146
[White Rabbit] A sincere "thank you"

15:17.230 --> 15:22.521
to you all and the government
of these United States of the Earth realm

15:22.605 --> 15:26.605
for picking up
the rest of my amulet for me!

15:27.105 --> 15:28.146
[thump]

15:29.688 --> 15:32.771
God bless America!

15:52.355 --> 15:53.855
[tauntingly] Hmm. Hmm.

15:53.938 --> 15:56.605
Oh, shit! Our bullets don't affect him!

15:56.688 --> 15:57.938
[Sentry] His DNA is different!

15:58.521 --> 15:59.855
A new evolution!

16:04.480 --> 16:05.313
King!

16:17.563 --> 16:19.063
[somber choral music playing]

16:31.063 --> 16:33.146
What happened? Get them back!

16:33.230 --> 16:34.938
Get them back!

16:35.938 --> 16:38.313
[agent] Sir,
Air Force Two is on the runway.

16:38.396 --> 16:41.105
We need to get you
to a secure location right now, sir.

16:41.188 --> 16:42.688
[distressing music playing]

17:31.438 --> 17:34.313
Wow! And by my own brother!

17:34.396 --> 17:37.688
What? It's not my fault
you just stood there!

17:37.771 --> 17:40.396
Get your shit together!

17:40.480 --> 17:44.605
What use are any of us to the cause
if we can't kill one little girl?

17:44.688 --> 17:46.105
[shapeshifter] I don't know.

17:46.188 --> 17:50.396
Looks like she pruned you pretty good.

17:50.480 --> 17:55.271
None of this would be necessary if you'd
got the amulet when you were supposed to.

17:55.355 --> 17:58.355
And your rogue attempt
to fix it nearly exposed us.

17:58.438 --> 18:01.896
We will watch your blood drain

18:01.980 --> 18:03.980
for our leader.

18:04.563 --> 18:06.230
Where is your leader?

18:07.230 --> 18:09.355
[White Rabbit] Hello, Anders.

18:09.438 --> 18:13.646
I see my improvements
to your face are settling in nicely.

18:17.896 --> 18:19.396
No! No! What are you doing?

18:19.480 --> 18:22.230
I had to! He got to my daughters.

18:22.813 --> 18:25.688
And now he's going to destroy
the whole world!

18:25.771 --> 18:27.271
You've condemned us all!

18:27.355 --> 18:30.438
What good is saving the world
if I can't save my own family?

18:31.771 --> 18:33.730
[energy crackling]

18:38.438 --> 18:40.771
[White Rabbit bellowing]

18:43.771 --> 18:44.938
Fuck was that?

18:47.855 --> 18:48.855
The amulet.

18:49.480 --> 18:50.480
He did it.

18:51.396 --> 18:53.396
[distressing choral music intensifies]

18:55.146 --> 18:56.146
[Dante straining]

19:02.646 --> 19:06.230
You have the amulet and the sword,
transmitter and decoder.

19:06.313 --> 19:08.563
Why… Why aren't you using them?

19:08.646 --> 19:10.563
Why not open the rift, here and now?

19:10.646 --> 19:11.730
[sighs dramatically]

19:11.813 --> 19:14.855
Shame. I really had
higher hopes for you, Doctor.

19:15.563 --> 19:17.313
You're still missing a piece.

19:17.396 --> 19:18.605
It needs some kind of…

19:18.688 --> 19:20.146
Uh… Uh…

19:20.230 --> 19:21.521
Decryption key.

19:21.605 --> 19:22.813
There it is.

19:22.896 --> 19:25.313
That sharp mind I've heard about.

19:25.396 --> 19:28.271
Sadly limited by its service
to your master's profits.

19:28.355 --> 19:31.396
You're going to thank me
when the wall comes down.

19:31.480 --> 19:35.605
Then you'll see
what true freedom looks like.

19:37.771 --> 19:39.146
[blade rasps]

19:50.021 --> 19:50.938
[Anders yelping]

19:51.021 --> 19:53.438
Let's make this convincing.

19:54.896 --> 19:56.105
Not again!

19:56.688 --> 19:58.105
[Anders wails]

19:58.188 --> 20:00.521
[White Rabbit hums jauntily]

20:07.646 --> 20:08.771
[wheezes hoarsely]

20:09.355 --> 20:11.230
[grunts, pants]

20:12.813 --> 20:15.355
No one said
the apocalypse would come easy.

20:17.438 --> 20:18.938
[Dr. Fisher] Hey, Rabbit!

20:20.438 --> 20:22.313
Hop your way out of this!

20:29.105 --> 20:30.355
[muffled explosion]

20:33.480 --> 20:35.813
See? Told you there was a rabbit!

20:36.646 --> 20:39.521
Hey, don't his necklace
look kind of like your necklace,

20:39.605 --> 20:41.355
but with the other half of it?

20:41.438 --> 20:43.021
[Dante straining]

20:46.813 --> 20:48.313
-[beeping]
-[Dante gasps]

20:49.396 --> 20:51.730
Whoa! I… I'm stronger than I thought.

20:54.646 --> 20:56.896
[tense industrial music playing]

21:17.605 --> 21:18.605
[children cheering]

21:18.688 --> 21:21.771
That's my boy! [laughs]

21:23.438 --> 21:25.730
Ta-ta! Have to run.

21:40.730 --> 21:42.980
[winged demon] We go now.

21:43.063 --> 21:46.271
Bloody hell.
Just when I was about to kill her.

21:46.355 --> 21:48.480
Just when you were about to kill her?

21:48.563 --> 21:50.480
Just when I was about to kill her!

22:01.188 --> 22:02.730
[engine revs]

22:02.813 --> 22:05.938
I'll get it back, Mom. I promise.

22:06.021 --> 22:08.396
["Last Resort" by Papa Roach playing]

22:09.313 --> 22:13.688
♪ Cut my life into pieces
This is my last resort ♪

22:13.771 --> 22:15.063
He's here.

22:15.146 --> 22:17.771
♪ Suffocation, no breathing
Don't give a fuck… ♪

22:17.855 --> 22:19.438
You have your orders.

22:21.730 --> 22:24.313
♪ This is my last resort ♪

22:25.730 --> 22:27.396
[rowdy rap metal music playing]

22:29.396 --> 22:31.813
All right, now I'm pissed.

22:33.771 --> 22:35.355
♪ Suffocation, no breathing ♪

22:35.438 --> 22:38.146
♪ Don't give a fuck
If I cut my arm bleeding ♪

22:38.230 --> 22:40.271
♪ Do you even care if I die bleeding? ♪

22:40.355 --> 22:43.938
♪ Would it be wrong, would it be right
If I took my life tonight? ♪

22:44.021 --> 22:45.605
♪ Chances are that I might ♪

22:45.688 --> 22:47.688
♪ Mutilation out of sight ♪

22:47.771 --> 22:49.980
♪ And I'm contemplatin' suicide ♪

22:50.063 --> 22:53.021
♪ 'Cause I'm losin' my sight
Losin' my mind ♪

22:53.105 --> 22:55.521
♪ Wish somebody would tell me I'm fine ♪

22:55.605 --> 22:57.938
♪ Losin' my sight, losin' my mind ♪

22:58.021 --> 23:00.771
♪ Wish somebody would tell me I'm fine ♪

23:04.063 --> 23:04.980
[brakes screech]

23:05.855 --> 23:07.146
♪ I never realized I was spread too thin ♪

23:07.230 --> 23:08.230
Nice one, bro!

23:08.313 --> 23:10.938
♪ Till it was too late
And I was empty within ♪

23:11.021 --> 23:13.063
♪ Feeding on chaos and living in sin ♪

23:13.146 --> 23:15.396
♪ Downward spiral, where do I begin? ♪

23:15.980 --> 23:17.771
♪ It all started when I lost my mother ♪

23:17.855 --> 23:20.730
♪ No love for myself
And no love for another ♪

23:20.813 --> 23:23.063
♪ To find a love upon a higher level ♪

23:23.146 --> 23:25.230
♪ Finding nothing but
Questions and devils ♪

23:25.313 --> 23:28.313
♪ 'Cause I'm losing my sight
Losing my mind ♪

23:28.396 --> 23:30.855
♪ Wish somebody would tell me I'm fine ♪

23:30.938 --> 23:33.438
♪ Losing my sight, losing my mind ♪

23:33.521 --> 23:35.855
♪ Wish somebody would tell me I'm… ♪

23:35.938 --> 23:37.021
Damn, he's cool.

23:39.521 --> 23:40.771
[engine revs]

23:47.521 --> 23:49.646
[impatiently] Come on!
Come on, come on, come on.

23:49.730 --> 23:50.730
You can do it.

23:51.313 --> 23:53.605
I believe in you.

24:03.063 --> 24:06.480
Hey, while I've got you here,
what's it like being a demon?

24:06.563 --> 24:07.855
Do you have to be evil?

24:09.021 --> 24:11.230
Like, if someone was only part demon,

24:11.313 --> 24:13.146
if maybe their dad was possibly one,

24:13.230 --> 24:14.771
but their mom was a human,

24:14.855 --> 24:16.855
you think they'd get a choice, right?

24:24.521 --> 24:25.771
Thanks for the talk!

24:25.855 --> 24:27.355
You're a great listener!

24:29.438 --> 24:30.646
♪ Cut my life into pieces ♪

24:30.730 --> 24:32.646
That's it. Let it out.

24:33.230 --> 24:34.313
Let it out!

24:34.813 --> 24:36.896
♪ Suffocation, no breathing ♪

24:36.980 --> 24:39.396
♪ Don't give a fuck
If I cut my arm bleeding ♪

24:39.480 --> 24:40.730
[Mary] You two all right?

24:41.230 --> 24:45.396
Yeah, only until that killer Beanie Baby
decides to end the world.

24:45.480 --> 24:46.896
I'm working on that.

24:46.980 --> 24:49.021
You put a tracking device on the amulet?

24:49.105 --> 24:50.396
Just in case.

24:50.480 --> 24:51.313
What is it?

24:52.021 --> 24:53.230
How far away are they?

24:53.730 --> 24:55.855
Almost a mile. That means…

25:00.105 --> 25:01.105
[energy crackling]

25:09.688 --> 25:12.605
♪ Can't go on ♪

25:14.438 --> 25:17.688
♪ Living this way ♪

25:19.855 --> 25:21.063
♪ Nothing's all ♪

25:21.146 --> 25:22.188
Jackpot!

25:22.271 --> 25:24.105
[epic symphonic metal music building]

25:25.313 --> 25:26.146
♪ Right ♪

25:26.230 --> 25:27.271
[high-pitched beeping]

25:27.355 --> 25:28.355
[song halts]

25:34.521 --> 25:35.521
[White Rabbit sighs]

25:36.688 --> 25:38.480
-[Dante gurgles]
-[White Rabbit hums jauntily]

25:39.563 --> 25:40.563
[White Rabbit laughs]

25:41.688 --> 25:44.105
[sighs] Mmm? Mmm.

25:44.188 --> 25:48.230
It seems I still need to push you harder,

25:49.480 --> 25:51.105
son of Sparda.

25:51.188 --> 25:53.188
[eerie, distressing music playing]

25:57.021 --> 25:59.438
[shapeshifter gurgles, trills]

25:59.521 --> 26:02.646
It's your lucky day.

26:02.730 --> 26:07.980
See, my power works
off of quantum mirroring.

26:08.063 --> 26:11.646
I can only take on a new body

26:11.730 --> 26:16.355
if I'm copying
a form made of living tissue,

26:16.980 --> 26:20.605
which means I need to keep you alive.

26:29.188 --> 26:30.563
One of you.

26:34.813 --> 26:35.813
["Devils Never Cry" plays]

26:35.896 --> 26:37.271
♪ Bless me ♪

26:37.355 --> 26:43.355
♪ With the leaf off of the tree ♪

26:43.438 --> 26:47.271
♪ On it, I see ♪

26:47.355 --> 26:51.230
♪ The freedom reign ♪

26:51.313 --> 26:55.105
♪ We are falling ♪

26:55.188 --> 26:58.938
♪ The light is calling ♪

26:59.021 --> 27:02.855
♪ Tears inside me ♪

27:02.938 --> 27:06.813
♪ Calm me down ♪

27:06.896 --> 27:10.605
♪ Midnight calling ♪

27:10.688 --> 27:14.521
♪ Mist of resolving ♪

27:14.605 --> 27:16.563
♪ Crown me ♪

27:16.646 --> 27:22.396
♪ With the pure, green leaf ♪

27:22.480 --> 27:26.271
♪ Praise to my father ♪

27:26.355 --> 27:30.188
♪ Blessed by the water ♪

27:30.271 --> 27:34.063
♪ Black light, dark sky ♪

27:34.355 --> 27:35.855
IN MEMORY OF KEVIN CONROY
(1955-2022)

27:35.938 --> 27:39.021
♪ The devil's cry ♪